  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>Query Optimization Explorer</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Query Optimization Explorer</h1>\n\n<p>This is a plain, interactive explorer for query optimization concepts. It emphasizes functional interactivity over visual polish. Use the controls below to build a query, adjust statistics, enable indexes, and try different optimizer algorithms (dynamic programming, greedy, randomized, genetic-like). You can step through the DP optimization process, view plan space, compare and simulate plans, and save/load state as JSON.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<!-- Query & Statistics -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Tables & Statistics (add up to 6)</legend>\n  <div>\n    <label>Number of tables:\n      <select id=\"numTables\">\n        <option>2</option>\n        <option selected>3</option>\n        <option>4</option>\n        <option>5</option>\n        <option>6</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n    <button id=\"resetDefaults\">Reset to Defaults</button>\n    <button id=\"randomizeQuery\">Randomize Query</button>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"tablesContainer\"></div>\n  <p>For each table specify estimated rows and whether the table is included in the query.</p>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Predicates -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Join Predicates</legend>\n  <div id=\"predicatesContainer\"></div>\n  <p>Enable predicates between table pairs and set selectivities (0.0 - 1.0). Lower selectivity means fewer rows after join.</p>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Indexes -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Indexes & Hints</legend>\n  <div id=\"indexesContainer\"></div>\n  <p>Enable simple single-column index hints. Indexes reduce scan cost for that table for selective predicates.</p>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Cost Model & Join Algorithms -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Cost Model & Algorithm Options</legend>\n  <div>\n    <label>CPU weight (multiplier):\n      <input type=\"number\" id=\"cpuWeight\" value=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" min=\"0\">\n    </label>\n    <label>IO weight (multiplier):\n      <input type=\"number\" id=\"ioWeight\" value=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" min=\"0\">\n    </label>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <label>Join algorithm preference:\n      <select id=\"joinAlgPreference\">\n        <option value=\"auto\">Auto choose cheapest per join</option>\n        <option value=\"hash\">Hash Join</option>\n        <option value=\"merge\">Merge Join</option>\n        <option value=\"nested\">Nested Loops</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n    <label>Join style:\n      <select id=\"joinStyle\">\n        <option value=\"any\">Allow bushy/left-deep</option>\n        <option value=\"leftdeep\">Left-deep only</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n    <label>\n      <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"allowCartesian\"> Allow Cartesian joins (no predicate)\n    </label>\n  </div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Optimizer Controls -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Optimizer Controls</legend>\n  <div>\n    <label>Optimizer:\n      <select id=\"optimizer\">\n        <option value=\"dp\">Dynamic Programming (exhaustive)</option>\n        <option value=\"greedy\">Greedy (heuristic)</option>\n        <option value=\"random\">Randomized (permutations)</option>\n        <option value=\"genetic\">Genetic-like</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n    <label>Random iterations:\n      <input type=\"number\" id=\"randomIters\" value=\"200\" min=\"1\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Genetic iterations:\n      <input type=\"number\" id=\"genIters\" value=\"100\" min=\"1\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Population size:\n      <input type=\"number\" id=\"genPopulation\" value=\"30\" min=\"2\">\n    </label>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <button id=\"runOptimizer\">Run Optimizer (full)</button>\n    <button id=\"startDP\">Start DP (step mode)</button>\n    <button id=\"dpNext\">DP Step Forward</button>\n    <button id=\"dpPrev\">DP Step Back</button>\n    <button id=\"runDPToEnd\">Run DP to End</button>\n    <button id=\"runGreedy\">Run Greedy</button>\n    <button id=\"runRandom\">Run Randomized</button>\n    <button id=\"runGenetic\">Run Genetic-like</button>\n    <button id=\"evaluateManual\">Evaluate Manual Order</button>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <label>Manual join order (comma separated table names):\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"manualOrder\" placeholder=\"A,B,C\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Manual join algorithm for joins (comma separated or single):\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"manualJoinAlgs\" placeholder=\"hash,merge\">\n    </label>\n  </div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Plan Space and DP State -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Plan Space & DP State</legend>\n  <div>\n    <button id=\"showAllPlans\">Show All Evaluated Plans</button>\n    <button id=\"showBest\">Show Best Plan</button>\n    <button id=\"exportState\">Export State JSON</button>\n    <button id=\"importState\">Import State JSON</button>\n    <button id=\"clearHistory\">Clear History</button>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <label>State JSON:\n      <textarea id=\"stateJson\" rows=\"4\" cols=\"80\"></textarea>\n    </label>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <h3>DP State (subsets with best cost)</h3>\n    <pre id=\"dpStatePre\"></pre>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <h3>Plan Space (sorted by cost)</h3>\n    <pre id=\"planSpacePre\"></pre>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <h3>Best Plan</h3>\n    <pre id=\"bestPlanPre\"></pre>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <h3>History / Steps</h3>\n    <pre id=\"historyPre\"></pre>\n  </div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<!-- Simulation -->\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Plan Execution Simulator</legend>\n  <div>\n    <button id=\"simulatePlan\">Simulate Best Plan</button>\n    <button id=\"simulateManual\">Simulate Manual Plan</button>\n    <label>Simulation step:\n      <input type=\"range\" id=\"simStep\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" value=\"0\">\n    </label>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <h3>Execution Trace</h3>\n    <pre id=\"executionPre\"></pre>\n  </div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<script>\n/*\n  Query Optimization Explorer - Plain, interactive, single-file.\n  - Many controls to explore dynamic programming, heuristics, and plan evaluation.\n  - Minimal visual styling; all functionality implemented in JavaScript.\n*/\n\n// --- Utility helpers ---\nfunction $(id) { return document.getElementById(id); }\nfunction clone(o) { return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(o)); }\n\n// --- Global state ---\nlet state = {\n  tables: [], // {name, rows, included}\n  predicates: {}, // key \"A|B\" -> {enabled, sel}\n  indexes: {}, // tableName -> {enabled}\n  cpuWeight: 1,\n  ioWeight: 1,\n  joinAlgPref: 'auto',\n  allowCartesian: false,\n  joinStyle: 'any',\n  optimizer: 'dp',\n  planSpace: [], // evaluated plans\n  bestPlan: null,\n  dpSteps: [], // snapshot per DP subset-size step\n  dpPointer: -1,\n  history: [],\n};\n\n// --- Initialization: default tables & UI wiring ---\nfunction initDefaults(n) {\n  state.tables = [];\n  const defaultRows = [1000, 5000, 200, 800, 1200, 300];\n  const names = ['A','B','C','D','E','F'];\n  for (let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    state.tables.push({name:names[i], rows: defaultRows[i] || 1000, included:true});\n  }\n  // default predicates: A-B, B-C, C-D etc enabled with moderate selectivity\n  state.predicates = {};\n  for (let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    for (let j=i+1;j<n;j++){\n      const key = pairKey(state.tables[i].name, state.tables[j].name);\n      const sel = (j===i+1) ? 0.1 : 0.5; // adjacent more selective\n      state.predicates[key] = {enabled: (j===i+1), sel: sel};\n    }\n  }\n  state.indexes = {};\n  state.tables.forEach(t => state.indexes[t.name] = {enabled:false});\n  state.cpuWeight = parseFloat($('cpuWeight').value);\n  state.ioWeight = parseFloat($('ioWeight').value);\n  state.joinAlgPref = $('joinAlgPreference').value;\n  state.allowCartesian = $('allowCartesian').checked;\n  state.joinStyle = $('joinStyle').value;\n  state.optimizer = $('optimizer').value;\n  state.planSpace = [];\n  state.bestPlan = null;\n  state.dpSteps = [];\n  state.dpPointer = -1;\n  state.history = [];\n}\n\nfunction pairKey(a,b){\n  return a < b ? (a + '|' + b) : (b + '|' + a);\n}\n\nfunction buildTablesUI(){\n  const container = $('tablesContainer');\n  container.innerHTML = '';\n  state.tables.forEach((t, idx)=>{\n    const div = document.createElement('div');\n    div.innerHTML =\n      '<label><input type=\"checkbox\" data-idx=\"'+idx+'\" class=\"tableIncluded\" '+(t.included?'checked':'')+'> Include '+t.name+'</label> ' +\n      '<label> Rows: <input type=\"number\" class=\"tableRows\" data-idx=\"'+idx+'\" value=\"'+t.rows+'\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\"></label>';\n    container.appendChild(div);\n  });\n  // wire events\n  Array.from(document.getElementsByClassName('tableIncluded')).forEach(el=>{\n    el.addEventListener('change', (e)=>{\n      const idx = parseInt(e.target.dataset.idx);\n      state.tables[idx].included = e.target.checked;\n    });\n  });\n  Array.from(document.getElementsByClassName('tableRows')).forEach(el=>{\n    el.addEventListener('change', (e)=>{\n      const idx = parseInt(e.target.dataset.idx);\n      let v = parseInt(e.target.value) || 1;\n      state.tables[idx].rows = Math.max(1, v);\n    });\n  });\n}\n\nfunction buildPredicatesUI(){\n  const container = $('predicatesContainer');\n  container.innerHTML = '';\n  const includedTables = state.tables.map(t=>t.name);\n  for (let i=0;i<includedTables.length;i++){\n    for (let j=i+1;j<includedTables.length;j++){\n      const a = includedTables[i], b = includedTables[j];\n      const key = pairKey(a,b);\n      const pred = state.predicates[key] || {enabled:false, sel:0.1};\n      const div = document.createElement('div');\n      div.innerHTML = '<label><input type=\"checkbox\" data-key=\"'+key+'\" class=\"predEnabled\" '+(pred.enabled ? 'checked' : '')+'> Predicate '+a+'-'+b+'</label> ' +\n        '<label> Selectivity: <input type=\"number\" step=\"0.01\" min=\"0.0001\" max=\"1\" data-key=\"'+key+'\" class=\"predSel\" value=\"'+pred.sel+'\"></label>';\n      container.appendChild(div);\n    }\n  }\n  Array.from(document.getElementsByClassName('predEnabled')).forEach(el=>{\n    el.addEventListener('change', (e)=>{\n      const key = e.target.dataset.key;\n      if (!state.predicates[key]) state.predicates[key] = {enabled:false, sel:0.1};\n      state.predicates[key].enabled = e.target.checked;\n    });\n  });\n  Array.from(document.getElementsByClassName('predSel')).forEach(el=>{\n    el.addEventListener('change', (e)=>{\n      const key = e.target.dataset.key;\n      if (!state.predicates[key]) state.predicates[key] = {enabled:false, sel:0.1};\n      let v = parseFloat(e.target.value);\n      if (isNaN(v) || v<=0) v = 0.001;\n      if (v>1) v = 1;\n      state.predicates[key].sel = v;\n    });\n  });\n}\n\nfunction buildIndexesUI(){\n  const container = $('indexesContainer');\n  container.innerHTML = '';\n  state.tables.forEach(t=>{\n    const idx = state.indexes[t.name] || {enabled:false};\n    const div = document.createElement('div');\n    div.innerHTML = '<label><input type=\"checkbox\" data-name=\"'+t.name+'\" class=\"idxEnabled\" '+(idx.enabled ? 'checked' : '')+'> Index on '+t.name+'</label>';\n    container.appendChild(div);\n  });\n  Array.from(document.getElementsByClassName('idxEnabled')).forEach(el=>{\n    el.addEventListener('change', (e)=>{\n      const name = e.target.dataset.name;\n      if (!state.indexes[name]) state.indexes[name] = {enabled:false};\n      state.indexes[name].enabled = e.target.checked;\n    });\n  });\n}\n\nfunction refreshAllUI(){\n  buildTablesUI();\n  buildPredicatesUI();\n  buildIndexesUI();\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n}\n\n// --- Cost & evaluation model ---\n// Basic cost estimation functions: compute join selectivity between two sets, cost formulas.\nfunction getIncludedTableNames(){\n  return state.tables.filter(t=>t.included).map(t=>t.name);\n}\nfunction getTableRows(name){\n  const t = state.tables.find(x=>x.name===name);\n  return t ? t.rows : 0;\n}\nfunction predicateBetween(a,b){\n  const key = pairKey(a,b);\n  return state.predicates[key] && state.predicates[key].enabled ? state.predicates[key].sel : null;\n}\nfunction combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leftTables, rightTables){\n  // multiply selectivities of any enabled predicates between any pair across groups.\n  // If none and allowCartesian is false, treat selectivity high (0) to penalize; but we allow optionally.\n  let found = false;\n  let sel = 1.0;\n  for (let la of leftTables){\n    for (let rb of rightTables){\n      const p = predicateBetween(la, rb);\n      if (p !== null && p !== undefined){\n        found = true;\n        sel *= p;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  if (!found){\n    return state.allowCartesian ? 1.0 : 1.0; // we'll penalize via cost not selectivity (cost big if cross)\n  }\n  return Math.max(0.000001, sel);\n}\n\nfunction chooseJoinAlgorithm(leftRows, rightRows, sel){\n  // If preference is auto, pick fastest estimated join algorithm based on simple heuristic.\n  const pref = $('joinAlgPreference').value;\n  if (pref !== 'auto') return pref;\n  // heuristic: if one side very small -> nested loops; else hash join\n  if (Math.min(leftRows, rightRows) < 100) return 'nested';\n  return 'hash';\n}\n\nfunction joinCostEstimate(leftRows, rightRows, sel, joinAlg, leftHasIndex, rightHasIndex){\n  // rows after join\n  let rows = Math.max(1, Math.floor(leftRows * rightRows * sel));\n  // base CPU cost proportional to inputs * sel\n  let cpu = leftRows * rightRows * sel;\n  // IO cost: scanning inputs (reduced by index if available and selective)\n  let io = leftRows + rightRows;\n  if (leftHasIndex) io *= 0.3;\n  if (rightHasIndex) io *= 0.3;\n  // algorithm multipliers\n  let algMult = 1.0;\n  if (joinAlg === 'nested') algMult = 2.5;\n  if (joinAlg === 'merge') algMult = 1.2;\n  if (joinAlg === 'hash') algMult = 1.0;\n  const cpuW = parseFloat($('cpuWeight').value) || 1;\n  const ioW = parseFloat($('ioWeight').value) || 1;\n  const cost = algMult * (cpuW * cpu + ioW * io);\n  return {cost: cost, rows: rows};\n}\n\n// Evaluate a plan tree recursively. Tree structure:\n// leaf: {type:'leaf', name:'A'}\n// join: {type:'join', left: {...}, right:{...}, alg: 'hash'}; We'll compute cost and rows and add metadata.\nfunction evaluatePlanTree(node){\n  if (node.type === 'leaf'){\n    node.rows = getTableRows(node.name);\n    node.cost = 0;\n    node.desc = node.name;\n    return node;\n  }\n  // evaluate children\n  evaluatePlanTree(node.left);\n  evaluatePlanTree(node.right);\n  const leftRows = node.left.rows;\n  const rightRows = node.right.rows;\n  // determine predicate selectivity across left/right groups\n  const leftLeafNames = leafNames(node.left);\n  const rightLeafNames = leafNames(node.right);\n  const sel = combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leftLeafNames, rightLeafNames);\n  const leftIndex = anyIndexOnSet(leftLeafNames);\n  const rightIndex = anyIndexOnSet(rightLeafNames);\n  const alg = node.alg || chooseJoinAlgorithm(leftRows, rightRows, sel);\n  const jc = joinCostEstimate(leftRows, rightRows, sel, alg, leftIndex, rightIndex);\n  node.joinSelectivity = sel;\n  node.alg = alg;\n  node.rows = jc.rows;\n  node.localCost = jc.cost;\n  node.cost = (node.left.cost || 0) + (node.right.cost || 0) + node.localCost;\n  node.desc = '(' + node.left.desc + ' ⋈ ' + node.right.desc + ')';\n  return node;\n}\n\nfunction leafNames(node){\n  if (node.type === 'leaf') return [node.name];\n  return leafNames(node.left).concat(leafNames(node.right));\n}\nfunction anyIndexOnSet(names){\n  for (const n of names) if (state.indexes[n] && state.indexes[n].enabled) return true;\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction treeToString(node, indent=\"\"){\n  if (!node) return \"\";\n  if (node.type === 'leaf') return indent + node.name + ' [rows=' + node.rows + ']\\n';\n  let s = indent + 'JOIN alg=' + node.alg + ' sel=' + (node.joinSelectivity||1).toFixed(4) + ' localCost=' + (node.localCost||0).toFixed(2) + ' rows=' + node.rows + ' totalCost=' + (node.cost||0).toFixed(2) + '\\n';\n  s += treeToString(node.left, indent + '  ');\n  s += treeToString(node.right, indent + '  ');\n  return s;\n}\n\n// --- Plan generation / enumeration ---\n\nfunction makeLeaf(name){ return {type:'leaf', name:name}; }\n\n// DP enumeration: for included tables generate best plan per subset mask\nfunction runDynamicProgramming(stepMode){\n  const tables = getIncludedTableNames();\n  const n = tables.length;\n  if (n < 2) { alert('Need at least 2 included tables to join.'); return; }\n  if (n > 6) {\n    if (!confirm('Exhaustive DP over more than 6 tables may be slow. Continue?')) return;\n  }\n  // map table index\n  const idxOf = {};\n  tables.forEach((t,i)=>idxOf[t]=i);\n  const totalMasks = 1<<n;\n  const best = new Array(totalMasks).fill(null); // best[mask] = {plan,cost,rows}\n  // initialize singletons\n  for (let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    const mask = 1<<i;\n    const leaf = makeLeaf(tables[i]);\n    evaluatePlanTree(leaf);\n    best[mask] = {plan:leaf, cost:leaf.cost, rows:leaf.rows};\n  }\n  // if stepMode we will create snapshots after processing each subset-size\n  const steps = [];\n  steps.push(cloneDPStateSnapshot(best, n));\n  for (let size=2; size<=n; size++){\n    // iterate masks with popcount == size\n    for (let mask=0; mask<totalMasks; mask++){\n      if (popcount(mask) !== size) continue;\n      let bestPlan = null;\n      let bestCost = Infinity;\n      // iterate non-empty proper submasks L of mask\n      // for efficiency iterate L = (mask-1) & mask ... typical submask enumeration\n      for (let left = (mask-1) & mask; left > 0; left = (left-1) & mask){\n        const right = mask ^ left;\n        if (right === 0) continue;\n        // If left-deep only and left is not singleton (to ensure left-deep?), we can enforce strategy:\n        if ($('joinStyle').value === 'leftdeep'){\n          // only consider left as a continuous prefix in some permutation - hard to enforce here simply.\n          // Simple enforcement: only allow left to be a singleton (grow left-deep by adding one table at a time)\n          if (popcount(left) !== 1) continue;\n        }\n        const leftBest = best[left];\n        const rightBest = best[right];\n        if (!leftBest || !rightBest) continue;\n        // combine trees\n        // choose join alg (auto or pref)\n        const alg = $('joinAlgPreference').value === 'auto' ? chooseJoinAlgorithm(leftBest.rows, rightBest.rows, combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leafNames(leftBest.plan), leafNames(rightBest.plan))) : $('joinAlgPreference').value;\n        const node = {type:'join', left: clone(leftBest.plan), right: clone(rightBest.plan), alg: alg};\n        evaluatePlanTree(node);\n        // penalize Cartesian joins if disallowed\n        const leftNames = leafNames(node.left);\n        const rightNames = leafNames(node.right);\n        const sel = combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leftNames, rightNames);\n        if (!state.allowCartesian && !hasPredicateBetweenSets(leftNames, rightNames) && sel===1.0){\n          node.cost *= 1000; // big penalty\n        }\n        if (node.cost < bestCost){\n          bestCost = node.cost;\n          bestPlan = node;\n        }\n      }\n      if (bestPlan){\n        best[mask] = {plan: bestPlan, cost: bestCost, rows: bestPlan.rows};\n      }\n    }\n    steps.push(cloneDPStateSnapshot(best, n));\n  }\n  // final best for full mask\n  const fullMask = (1<<n) - 1;\n  const final = best[fullMask];\n  state.planSpace = collectAllPlansFromDP(best, n);\n  state.bestPlan = final ? final.plan : null;\n  state.dpSteps = steps;\n  state.dpPointer = steps.length - 1;\n  state.history.push({action:'dp_complete', details:{tables:tables.slice(), best: state.bestPlan ? state.bestPlan.desc : null}});\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n  if (!stepMode){\n    alert('DP completed. Best cost: ' + (state.bestPlan ? state.bestPlan.cost.toFixed(2) : 'n/a'));\n  } else {\n    alert('DP started in step mode. Use Step Forward to move through subset sizes.');\n  }\n}\n\nfunction cloneDPStateSnapshot(bestArr, n){\n  // create human-friendly snapshot: for each mask store best desc and cost\n  const snapshot = [];\n  const totalMasks = 1<<n;\n  for (let mask=1; mask<totalMasks; mask++){\n    const item = bestArr[mask];\n    snapshot.push({\n      mask: mask,\n      tables: maskToTableNames(mask,n),\n      bestDesc: item ? (item.plan.desc || leafNames(item.plan).join(',')) : null,\n      cost: item ? item.cost : null,\n      rows: item ? item.rows : null\n    });\n  }\n  return snapshot;\n}\n\nfunction maskToTableNames(mask, n){\n  const names = getIncludedTableNames();\n  const arr = [];\n  for (let i=0;i<n;i++) if (mask & (1<<i)) arr.push(names[i]);\n  return arr;\n}\nfunction popcount(x){ return x.toString(2).split('0').join('').length; }\nfunction hasPredicateBetweenSets(leftNames, rightNames){\n  for (let la of leftNames) for (let rb of rightNames) if (predicateBetween(la, rb) !== null) return true;\n  return false;\n}\nfunction collectAllPlansFromDP(bestArr, n){\n  const fullMask = (1<<n)-1;\n  const planList = [];\n  // traverse recursively from full mask collecting candidate plans by re-evaluating partitions (this produces one best plan per mask)\n  function collectForMask(mask){\n    const item = bestArr[mask];\n    if (!item) return;\n    planList.push(item.plan);\n    // recursively collect children plans\n    if (item.plan.type === 'join'){\n      collectPlanNodes(item.plan, planList);\n    }\n  }\n  collectForMask(fullMask);\n  // sort by cost (evaluatePlanTree may have already added costs)\n  const unique = dedupePlans(planList).map(p=>{ evaluatePlanTree(p); return p; });\n  unique.sort((a,b)=> (a.cost || 0) - (b.cost || 0));\n  return unique;\n}\nfunction collectPlanNodes(node, list){\n  if (!node) return;\n  if (node.type === 'leaf') return;\n  list.push(node.left);\n  list.push(node.right);\n  collectPlanNodes(node.left, list);\n  collectPlanNodes(node.right, list);\n}\nfunction dedupePlans(arr){\n  const seen = new Set();\n  const res = [];\n  arr.forEach(p=>{\n    const key = JSON.stringify(planSignature(p));\n    if (!seen.has(key)){ seen.add(key); res.push(p); }\n  });\n  return res;\n}\nfunction planSignature(node){\n  if (!node) return null;\n  if (node.type === 'leaf') return {t: 'L', name: node.name};\n  return {t: 'J', left: planSignature(node.left), right: planSignature(node.right), alg: node.alg};\n}\n\n// --- Heuristics and Randomized strategies ---\n\nfunction runGreedy(){\n  const tables = getIncludedTableNames();\n  if (tables.length < 2) { alert('Need at least 2 tables.'); return; }\n  // start with the table with smallest rows\n  let remaining = tables.slice();\n  remaining.sort((a,b)=>getTableRows(a)-getTableRows(b));\n  let currentPlan = makeLeaf(remaining.shift());\n  while (remaining.length){\n    let bestMerge = null;\n    let bestCost = Infinity;\n    let bestIdx = -1;\n    for (let i=0;i<remaining.length;i++){\n      const cand = makeLeaf(remaining[i]);\n      const node = {type:'join', left: clone(currentPlan), right: cand, alg: $('joinAlgPreference').value === 'auto' ? undefined : $('joinAlgPreference').value};\n      evaluatePlanTree(node);\n      if (!state.allowCartesian && !hasPredicateBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right)) && combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right))===1.0){\n        node.cost *= 1000;\n      }\n      if (node.cost < bestCost){\n        bestCost = node.cost;\n        bestMerge = node;\n        bestIdx = i;\n      }\n    }\n    if (bestMerge === null) break;\n    currentPlan = bestMerge;\n    remaining.splice(bestIdx, 1);\n  }\n  evaluatePlanTree(currentPlan);\n  state.planSpace = [currentPlan];\n  state.bestPlan = currentPlan;\n  state.history.push({action:'greedy', details:{best:currentPlan.desc}});\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n  alert('Greedy completed. Cost: ' + currentPlan.cost.toFixed(2));\n}\n\nfunction runRandomized(iterations){\n  const tables = getIncludedTableNames();\n  if (tables.length < 2) { alert('Need at least 2 tables.'); return; }\n  const plans = [];\n  for (let it=0; it<iterations; it++){\n    const perm = shuffle(tables.slice());\n    // build left-deep plan from permutation\n    let plan = makeLeaf(perm[0]);\n    for (let i=1;i<perm.length;i++){\n      const r = makeLeaf(perm[i]);\n      const node = {type:'join', left: clone(plan), right: r, alg: undefined};\n      evaluatePlanTree(node);\n      if (!state.allowCartesian && !hasPredicateBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right)) && combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right))===1.0){\n        node.cost *= 1000;\n      }\n      plan = node;\n    }\n    evaluatePlanTree(plan);\n    plans.push(plan);\n  }\n  plans.sort((a,b)=>a.cost - b.cost);\n  state.planSpace = plans;\n  state.bestPlan = plans[0];\n  state.history.push({action:'random', details:{iters:iterations, best: state.bestPlan.desc}});\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n  alert('Randomized search done. Best cost: ' + state.bestPlan.cost.toFixed(2));\n}\n\nfunction shuffle(arr){\n  for (let i=arr.length-1;i>0;i--){\n    const j = Math.floor(Math.random()*(i+1));\n    const tmp = arr[i]; arr[i]=arr[j]; arr[j]=tmp;\n  }\n  return arr;\n}\n\nfunction runGenetic(popSize, iter){\n  const tables = getIncludedTableNames();\n  if (tables.length < 2) { alert('Need at least 2 tables.'); return; }\n  // individual = permutation array\n  let population = [];\n  // initialize population randomly including a few heuristics\n  population.push(tables.slice().sort((a,b)=>getTableRows(a)-getTableRows(b))); // small-first\n  population.push(tables.slice().sort((a,b)=>getTableRows(b)-getTableRows(a))); // large-first\n  while (population.length < popSize){\n    population.push(shuffle(tables.slice()));\n  }\n  let evaluate = (perm) => {\n    let plan = makeLeaf(perm[0]);\n    for (let i=1;i<perm.length;i++){\n      const node = {type:'join', left: clone(plan), right: makeLeaf(perm[i]), alg: undefined};\n      evaluatePlanTree(node);\n      if (!state.allowCartesian && !hasPredicateBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right)) && combinedSelectivityBetweenSets(leafNames(node.left), leafNames(node.right))===1.0){\n        node.cost *= 1000;\n      }\n      plan = node;\n    }\n    evaluatePlanTree(plan);\n    return {perm: perm.slice(), plan: plan, cost: plan.cost};\n  };\n  // evaluate initial\n  let popEval = population.map(p=>evaluate(p));\n  for (let it=0; it<iter; it++){\n    // selection: keep top 50%\n    popEval.sort((a,b)=>a.cost-b.cost);\n    const survivors = popEval.slice(0, Math.max(2, Math.floor(popEval.length/2)));\n    // reproduce: cross-over pairs and mutate\n    const nextPop = survivors.map(s=>s.perm);\n    while (nextPop.length < popSize){\n      const a = survivors[Math.floor(Math.random()*survivors.length)].perm;\n      const b = survivors[Math.floor(Math.random()*survivors.length)].perm;\n      const child = crossoverPerm(a,b);\n      if (Math.random() < 0.2) mutatePerm(child);\n      nextPop.push(child);\n    }\n    popEval = nextPop.map(p=>evaluate(p));\n  }\n  popEval.sort((a,b)=>a.cost-b.cost);\n  state.planSpace = popEval.map(x=>x.plan);\n  state.bestPlan = popEval[0].plan;\n  state.history.push({action:'genetic', details:{iters:iter, pop:popSize, best: state.bestPlan.desc}});\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n  alert('Genetic-like search done. Best cost: ' + state.bestPlan.cost.toFixed(2));\n}\n\nfunction crossoverPerm(a,b){\n  // order crossover (OX)\n  const n = a.length;\n  const child = new Array(n).fill(null);\n  const i = Math.floor(Math.random()*n);\n  const j = Math.floor(Math.random()*n);\n  const s = Math.min(i,j), e = Math.max(i,j);\n  for (let k=s;k<=e;k++) child[k] = a[k];\n  let bi = 0;\n  for (let k=0;k<n;k++){\n    const idx = (e+1+k)%n;\n    while (child[idx] === null){\n      if (!a.includes(b[bi]) || child.includes(b[bi])) bi++;\n      if (bi >= b.length) break;\n      if (!child.includes(b[bi])) { child[idx] = b[bi]; bi++; break; }\n      bi++;\n    }\n  }\n  // fill left positions with elements from b in order\n  let pos = 0;\n  for (let x of b){\n    if (!child.includes(x)){\n      while (child[pos] !== null) pos++;\n      child[pos] = x;\n    }\n  }\n  return child;\n}\nfunction mutatePerm(p){\n  const i = Math.floor(Math.random()*p.length);\n  const j = Math.floor(Math.random()*p.length);\n  const tmp = p[i]; p[i]=p[j]; p[j]=tmp;\n}\n\n// --- Manual plan evaluation ---\nfunction evaluateManualPlan(){\n  const orderText = $('manualOrder').value.trim();\n  if (!orderText) { alert('Enter a manual join order.'); return; }\n  const tables = orderText.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s);\n  const included = getIncludedTableNames();\n  // validate\n  if (tables.length !== included.length || !tables.every(t=>included.includes(t))){\n    if (!confirm('Manual order does not exactly match included tables. Proceed with given names?')) {\n      return;\n    }\n  }\n  // join algs\n  let algs = $('manualJoinAlgs').value.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s);\n  if (algs.length === 0) algs = [undefined];\n  let plan = makeLeaf(tables[0]);\n  for (let i=1;i<tables.length;i++){\n    const alg = algs[(i-1) % algs.length] || undefined;\n    const node = {type:'join', left: clone(plan), right: makeLeaf(tables[i]), alg: alg};\n    evaluatePlanTree(node);\n    plan = node;\n  }\n  evaluatePlanTree(plan);\n  state.bestPlan = plan;\n  state.planSpace.unshift(plan);\n  state.history.push({action:'manual_eval', details:{order:tables, cost:plan.cost}});\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n  alert('Manual plan evaluated. Cost: ' + plan.cost.toFixed(2));\n}\n\n// --- DP step control ---\nfunction startDP(){\n  runDynamicProgramming(true);\n  state.dpPointer = 0;\n  showDPPointer();\n}\nfunction dpStepForward(){\n  if (!state.dpSteps || state.dpSteps.length === 0){ alert('No DP session. Click Start DP.'); return; }\n  if (state.dpPointer < state.dpSteps.length - 1) state.dpPointer++;\n  showDPPointer();\n}\nfunction dpStepBack(){\n  if (!state.dpSteps || state.dpSteps.length === 0){ alert('No DP session. Click Start DP.'); return; }\n  if (state.dpPointer > 0) state.dpPointer--;\n  showDPPointer();\n}\nfunction runDPToEnd(){\n  if (!state.dpSteps || state.dpSteps.length === 0) { alert('No DP session. Click Start DP.'); return; }\n  state.dpPointer = state.dpSteps.length - 1;\n  showDPPointer();\n}\nfunction showDPPointer(){\n  const dpStatePre = $('dpStatePre');\n  const ptr = state.dpPointer;\n  if (ptr < 0 || ptr >= state.dpSteps.length){ dpStatePre.textContent = 'No DP snapshot.'; return; }\n  const snap = state.dpSteps[ptr];\n  let s = 'DP snapshot step ' + ptr + ' (subsets processed up to size ' + ptr + ')\\n';\n  snap.forEach(it=>{\n    s += ' {' + it.tables.join(',') + '} -> ' + (it.bestDesc ? it.bestDesc : 'n/a') + ' cost=' + (it.cost ? it.cost.toFixed(2) : 'n/a') + '\\n';\n  });\n  dpStatePre.textContent = s;\n  $('historyPre').textContent = JSON.stringify(state.history, null, 2);\n}\n\n// --- Display & UI updates ---\nfunction updateComputedDisplays(){\n  // planSpace display\n  const ps = $('planSpacePre');\n  let s = '';\n  if (state.planSpace && state.planSpace.length){\n    state.planSpace.forEach((p,i)=>{\n      evaluatePlanTree(p); // refresh numbers\n      s += '[' + (i+1) + '] cost=' + p.cost.toFixed(2) + ' rows=' + p.rows + ' desc=' + (p.desc || leafNames(p).join(',')) + '\\n';\n    });\n  } else s = '(no plans evaluated yet)\\n';\n  ps.textContent = s;\n  // best plan\n  const bp = $('bestPlanPre');\n  if (state.bestPlan){\n    evaluatePlanTree(state.bestPlan);\n    bp.textContent = treeToString(state.bestPlan);\n  } else bp.textContent = '(no best plan)';\n  // dpState\n  showDPPointer();\n  // history\n  $('historyPre').textContent = state.history.map(h=>JSON.stringify(h)).join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction showAllPlans(){\n  if (!state.planSpace || state.planSpace.length===0){ alert('No evaluated plans yet. Run an optimizer or evaluate manually.'); return; }\n  let s = '';\n  state.planSpace.forEach((p,i)=>{\n    evaluatePlanTree(p);\n    s += '--- Plan #' + (i+1) + ' ---\\n';\n    s += treeToString(p);\n    s += '\\n';\n  });\n  alert('See plan list in the \"Plan Space\" area and \"Best Plan\".');\n}\n\n// Execution simulation\nfunction simulatePlan(plan, stepSliderId){\n  if (!plan){ alert('No plan to simulate.'); return; }\n  evaluatePlanTree(plan);\n  // flatten join nodes in order (left-deep execution order emulated by post-order)\n  const joinNodes = [];\n  function collectJoins(node){\n    if (!node) return;\n    if (node.type === 'join'){\n      collectJoins(node.left); collectJoins(node.right);\n      joinNodes.push(node);\n    }\n  }\n  collectJoins(plan);\n  // build trace\n  let trace = '';\n  let totalCost = 0;\n  joinNodes.forEach((jn, idx)=>{\n    trace += 'Step ' + (idx+1) + ': JOIN ' + jn.left.desc + ' ⋈ ' + jn.right.desc + '\\n';\n    trace += '  algorithm=' + jn.alg + ' selectivity=' + (jn.joinSelectivity||1).toFixed(6) + '\\n';\n    trace += '  leftRows=' + jn.left.rows + ' rightRows=' + jn.right.rows + ' resultRows=' + jn.rows + '\\n';\n    trace += '  localCost=' + (jn.localCost||0).toFixed(2) + ' totalSoFar=' + (totalCost + (jn.localCost||0)).toFixed(2) + '\\n\\n';\n    totalCost += (jn.localCost||0);\n  });\n  trace += 'Final estimated cost: ' + (plan.cost||0).toFixed(2) + '\\n';\n  $('executionPre').textContent = trace;\n  // configure slider\n  const slider = $('simStep');\n  slider.max = Math.max(0, joinNodes.length);\n  slider.value = 0;\n  slider.oninput = function(){\n    const step = parseInt(slider.value);\n    let partialTrace = '';\n    let runningCost = 0;\n    for (let i=0;i<step && i<joinNodes.length;i++){\n      const jn = joinNodes[i];\n      partialTrace += 'Step ' + (i+1) + ': JOIN ' + jn.left.desc + ' ⋈ ' + jn.right.desc + '\\n';\n      partialTrace += '  algorithm=' + jn.alg + ' selectivity=' + (jn.joinSelectivity||1).toFixed(6) + '\\n';\n      partialTrace += '  leftRows=' + jn.left.rows + ' rightRows=' + jn.right.rows + ' resultRows=' + jn.rows + '\\n';\n      partialTrace += '  localCost=' + (jn.localCost||0).toFixed(2) + ' totalSoFar=' + (runningCost + (jn.localCost||0)).toFixed(2) + '\\n\\n';\n      runningCost += (jn.localCost||0);\n    }\n    partialTrace += 'Partial estimated cost after ' + step + ' steps: ' + runningCost.toFixed(2) + '\\n';\n    $('executionPre').textContent = partialTrace;\n  };\n}\n\n// --- State import/export ---\nfunction exportStateJSON(){\n  const st = clone(state);\n  // don't export functions or large structures; keep essential parts\n  const exportObj = {\n    tables: st.tables,\n    predicates: st.predicates,\n    indexes: st.indexes,\n    cpuWeight: $('cpuWeight').value,\n    ioWeight: $('ioWeight').value,\n    joinAlgPreference: $('joinAlgPreference').value,\n    joinStyle: $('joinStyle').value,\n    allowCartesian: $('allowCartesian').checked\n  };\n  $('stateJson').value = JSON.stringify(exportObj, null, 2);\n}\nfunction importStateJSON(){\n  try{\n    const txt = $('stateJson').value;\n    if (!txt) { alert('Paste JSON into the State JSON textarea and click Import'); return; }\n    const obj = JSON.parse(txt);\n    if (!obj.tables) throw 'Invalid JSON: missing tables';\n    // apply\n    state.tables = obj.tables;\n    state.predicates = obj.predicates || {};\n    state.indexes = obj.indexes || {};\n    $('cpuWeight').value = obj.cpuWeight || 1;\n    $('ioWeight').value = obj.ioWeight || 1;\n    $('joinAlgPreference').value = obj.joinAlgPreference || 'auto';\n    $('joinStyle').value = obj.joinStyle || 'any';\n    $('allowCartesian').checked = obj.allowCartesian || false;\n    $('numTables').value = state.tables.length;\n    refreshAllUI();\n    alert('Imported state.');\n  }catch(e){\n    alert('Import failed: ' + e);\n  }\n}\n\n// --- Helpers & wiring events ---\nfunction updateConfigFromUI(){\n  state.cpuWeight = parseFloat($('cpuWeight').value) || 1;\n  state.ioWeight = parseFloat($('ioWeight').value) || 1;\n  state.joinAlgPref = $('joinAlgPreference').value;\n  state.allowCartesian = $('allowCartesian').checked;\n  state.joinStyle = $('joinStyle').value;\n  state.optimizer = $('optimizer').value;\n}\n\nfunction clearHistory(){\n  state.history = [];\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n}\n\nfunction randomizeQuery(){\n  const n = parseInt($('numTables').value);\n  initDefaults(n);\n  // random rows and random predicates\n  state.tables.forEach(t => {\n    t.rows = Math.max(10, Math.round(Math.exp(Math.random()*6)));\n    t.included = Math.random() > 0.1;\n  });\n  for (const k in state.predicates){\n    state.predicates[k].enabled = Math.random() > 0.6;\n    state.predicates[k].sel = +(Math.random()*(0.9)+0.01).toFixed(3);\n  }\n  // random indexes\n  for (const nname in state.indexes){\n    state.indexes[nname].enabled = Math.random() > 0.75;\n  }\n  refreshAllUI();\n  state.history.push({action:'randomize_query'});\n}\n\nfunction resetToDefaults(){\n  const n = parseInt($('numTables').value);\n  initDefaults(n);\n  refreshAllUI();\n  state.history.push({action:'reset_defaults'});\n}\n\nfunction exportAllPlansAsJSON(){\n  const exportPlans = state.planSpace.map(p => ({desc: p.desc || leafNames(p).join(','), cost: p.cost, rows: p.rows, tree: planSignature(p)}));\n  $('stateJson').value = JSON.stringify({plans: exportPlans}, null, 2);\n}\n\nfunction simulateBestPlan(){\n  if (!state.bestPlan){ alert('No best plan computed. Run an optimizer first.'); return; }\n  simulatePlan(clone(state.bestPlan));\n}\nfunction simulateManual(){\n  const orderText = $('manualOrder').value.trim();\n  if (!orderText){ alert('Provide a manual order to simulate.'); return; }\n  // evaluate manual plan into temp plan\n  const prevBest = state.bestPlan;\n  evaluateManualPlan();\n  simulatePlan(clone(state.bestPlan));\n  state.bestPlan = prevBest; // restore\n}\n\n// --- Event wiring ---\nwindow.onload = function(){\n  // initial\n  const n = parseInt($('numTables').value);\n  initDefaults(n);\n  refreshAllUI();\n\n  // wiring buttons\n  $('numTables').addEventListener('change', function(){\n    const nv = parseInt(this.value);\n    initDefaults(nv);\n    refreshAllUI();\n  });\n  $('resetDefaults').addEventListener('click', resetToDefaults);\n  $('randomizeQuery').addEventListener('click', randomizeQuery);\n\n  $('cpuWeight').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n  $('ioWeight').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n  $('joinAlgPreference').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n  $('allowCartesian').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n  $('joinStyle').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n  $('optimizer').addEventListener('change', updateConfigFromUI);\n\n  $('runOptimizer').addEventListener('click', function(){\n    updateConfigFromUI();\n    const opt = $('optimizer').value;\n    if (opt === 'dp') runDynamicProgramming(false);\n    else if (opt === 'greedy') runGreedy();\n    else if (opt === 'random') runRandomized(parseInt($('randomIters').value) || 200);\n    else if (opt === 'genetic') runGenetic(parseInt($('genPopulation').value) || 30, parseInt($('genIters').value) || 100);\n    updateComputedDisplays();\n  });\n\n  $('startDP').addEventListener('click', function(){ updateConfigFromUI(); startDP(); });\n  $('dpNext').addEventListener('click', dpStepForward);\n  $('dpPrev').addEventListener('click', dpStepBack);\n  $('runDPToEnd').addEventListener('click', runDPToEnd);\n  $('runGreedy').addEventListener('click', function(){ updateConfigFromUI(); runGreedy(); });\n  $('runRandom').addEventListener('click', function(){ updateConfigFromUI(); runRandomized(parseInt($('randomIters').value) || 200); });\n  $('runGenetic').addEventListener('click', function(){ updateConfigFromUI(); runGenetic(parseInt($('genPopulation').value) || 30, parseInt($('genIters').value) || 100); });\n\n  $('evaluateManual').addEventListener('click', evaluateManualPlan);\n  $('showAllPlans').addEventListener('click', showAllPlans);\n  $('showBest').addEventListener('click', function(){ if (!state.bestPlan) alert('No best plan'); else alert('Best plan shown in Best Plan area.'); });\n  $('exportState').addEventListener('click', exportStateJSON);\n  $('importState').addEventListener('click', importStateJSON);\n  $('clearHistory').addEventListener('click', clearHistory);\n  $('showAllPlans').addEventListener('click', updateComputedDisplays);\n  $('exportState').addEventListener('click', exportAllPlansAsJSON);\n\n  $('simulatePlan').addEventListener('click', simulateBestPlan);\n  $('simulateManual').addEventListener('click', simulateManual);\n  $('stateJson').addEventListener('change', function(){ /* optional */ });\n\n  // initial update\n  updateComputedDisplays();\n};\n\n// --- Misc helpers for plan collection and display ---\nfunction planToSimpleObject(node){\n  if (!node) return null;\n  if (node.type === 'leaf') return {type:'leaf', name:node.name, rows:node.rows};\n  return {type:'join', alg:node.alg, rows:node.rows, cost:node.cost, left:planToSimpleObject(node.left), right:planToSimpleObject(node.right)};\n}\n\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
